Topic Title: 16. 1. 2 Cytokinin’s

Content:
Cytokinin’s (Cyrtos - cell; kinesis - division) are the plant hormones that promote cell division or cytokinesis in plant cells. It was first isolated from Herring fish sperm. Zeatin was the cytokinin isolated from Zea mays. Cytokinin is found abundantly in liquid endosperm of coconut.
Physiological effects of cytokinin’s
Cytokinin induces cell division(cytokinesis) in the presence of auxins.
Cytokinin also causes cell enlargement.
Both auxins and cytokinin’s are essential for the formation of new organs from the callus in tissue culture (Morphogenesis).
Cytokinin’s promote the growth of lateral buds even in the presence of apical bud.
Application of cytokinin delays the process of ageing in plants. This is called Richmond Lang effect.

