R1 = 5 ohm, R2 = 3 ohm, R3 = 2 ohm, V = 10 Volt
R s = R1 + R2 + R3, Rs = 5 + 3 + 2 = 10, hence R s = 10 Ω
The current, I = V by R s equal to ten by ten equal to 1 ampere.

